    Liver Transpl
    Donor-recipient HLA-A mismatching is associated with hepatic artery thrombosis, sepsis, graft loss and reduced survival after liver transplantation.
In conclusion, HLA-A mismatching was associated with increased graft loss and mortality. The poorer outcome for The HLA mismatched group was due to hepatic artery thrombosis and sepsis and these complications occurred exclusively with HLA-A mismatched transplants. This suggests that HLA-A mismatching is important for post-transplant outcomes and knowledge of HLA-A status may enable enhanced surveillance and interventions to reduce risk of complications or stratified HLA-A matching in high-risk recipients.
